included.description:
@Google Play Store
1. Google Play Editorsâ Choice 
 I solely owned and led an entire UX design collaborating  with PM/Engs/UX/Merch. It launched in 17 countries : Japan, Korea, US, Taiwan, Hong kong, Russia, India, Brazil and so on with 22 articles and 10 titles for each launched market. 

2. Hyper tailored UX for Google Play Store in Japan and Korea
Japan and Korea(JPKR) are hugely important to Google Play Store. I led both design and initial user research and a cross functional pm/ux/merch/BD/marketing design sprints
I set design principles and provided hyper tailored design solutions : Denser UI, navigation UX, mini top chart, recommended categories, and deal and promotion.
Due to success of user satisfaction, the Store visits and acquisitions increase, scaled the features so they could be adopted as global Store patterns. 
I guided and influenced JPKR Play Store design to across Google such as Youtube, and NewsStand team.
